# ── npm-internal package CVEs ────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# npm ships as part of the Node.js base image and is present in the production
# container, but it is NEVER executed at runtime. The application runs purely
# as a `node` process (no `npm install`, no `npm run`). All CVEs listed here
# affect packages that are bundled INSIDE npm for npm's own use (package
# extraction, glob matching, IP formatting). They have zero attack surface in
# this container.
#
# Suppressed until the Node.js / npm project ships a base-image update that
# resolves them, at which point the daily Dependabot run or a Dockerfile
# base-image bump will clear them.

# tar <= 7.5.15  (npm@10 internal) — PAX size override file-smuggling.
# Fixed in tar@7.5.16; npm@10 has not yet shipped a release with it.
CVE-2026-53655

# brace-expansion  (npm@10 internal) — zero-step infinite loop DoS.
# Fixed in 1.1.13 / 2.0.3 / 3.0.2 / 5.0.5.
CVE-2026-33750

# picomatch < 2.3.2 / 3.0.2 / 4.0.4  (npm@10 internal) — ReDoS via extglob.
CVE-2026-33671

# picomatch < 2.3.2 / 3.0.2 / 4.0.4  (npm@10 internal) — POSIX bracket
# method injection / incorrect glob matching.
CVE-2026-33672

# ip-address < 10.1.1  (npm@10 internal) — XSS in Address6.group / .link.
# Only relevant if output is rendered in a browser; npm never does this.
CVE-2026-42338
